<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>What we need to do is one of the following:</p>

<ul><li>modify the InjectTemplateListener to not inject a template if a 404
is detected</li>
<li>modify ActionController::notFoundAction() to set an explicit template
on the returned view model</li>
</ul><p>The former is the easiest route, and allows you to use the site-wide 404
template easily. The second allows for per-controller 404 templates, but
would require code for inflecting the module namespace and controller
name -- which is currently encapsulated already in the
InjectTemplateListener.</p>

